<p>The <code>ON_BN_CLICKED</code> macro takes a button ID and a member function pointer. When the button is clicked the member function is called.</p>  <p>I have a member function, <code>foo</code>, who's pointer I have passed to <code>ON_BN_CLICKED</code>:</p>  <pre><code>ON_BN_CLICKED(1485, &amp;foo) </code></pre>  <p>But <code>foo</code> just directly calls outside the class to my business logic function:</p>  <pre><code>void presentation::foo() {     business-&gt;foo(); } </code></pre>  <p>I want to setup <code>ON_BN_CLICKED</code> to directly call this business logic function. Is this possible?</p>